JOHANNESBURG - Movement for Democratic Change president, Nelson Chamisa, has stressed their anti-government struggle is legitimate. He says the party's end goal is to overcome the political crisis in Zimbabwe and challenge Zimbabwean President, Emmerson Mnangagwa and his government. READ: Zimbabwe government panicking: Analyst Chamisa is callling police brutality in the country an international embarrassment. The MDC called off a planned shutdown of Harare on Friday after it failed to overturn a police ban on protest action. READ: Several injured as Zimbabwean police, protesters clash in Harare Friday's demonstrations would have been the first in a series of MDC-planned rallies. Police fired teargas and violently removed the large group gathered in the capital. The MDC has reported the arrest of over 60 people following the illegal protests.